reviews.text:
Unbelievable First Experience

Just tried Pizza Chef for the first time tonight, and I‚Äôm blown away. Pizza is incredible and you get more than your money's worth. Every slice was fresh, delicious, and way beyond my expectations for the price.

The staff were super friendly, the pickup was lightning-fast, and the whole process couldn‚Äôt have been easier. It‚Äôs a win-win: saving money, and treating yourself to amazing food. If you‚Äôre on the fence about trying new pizza spot, let this review push you over‚Äîyou won‚Äôt regret it.

10/10 experience. Thank you for the incredible pizza and the warm service! üçï‚ú®

It's a regular pizza shop but it's pretty good. I like the Ceasars salad with chicken too be honest. They have a grandma pizza no cheese for my husband and my kids like the regular pie so we all can eat here.

Best Italian pizza in Queens very good food high quality material cheese and sauce prices good very fast pick up or free delivery nice setting good atmosphere stuff very nice and helpful they have the best steam table and salad bar $ 9.75 for three courses choice of Rice or fresh pasta plus grilled chicken and fresh vegetables fish only $ 11.75 on lunch special.
The BEST Pizza around !!!  Fast delivery service and very nice workers.  A bit pricy but it's well worth the money.  Will never order from anyone else.  Pizza Chef, your the BEST !!!

In an Italian neighborhood, how do you get away with only 1 chicken cutlet in a  Chicken Parmigiano hero??  Weakest hero I have ever had - I expect a decent sandwich - sad!!  Update...ordered a full grandma pie today, and the pie was nothing more than tomato sauce on dough.  Was not even hot when they gave it to me.   Not impressed at all.

detailedReviews.author: John LaPorte
detailedReviews.text: I've been coming to Pizza Chef for over 50 years and for most of that time it has been great.  But over the last couple of years things have really deteriorated, particularly the service.  There are tables and a menu but you have to ask for it and I'm always told the prices are not updated. So, print a new menu.  Service is awful.  It's like pulling teeth to get someone to take an order at the table.  Last time I was told I had to order from the counter and carry it back.  Please.  If you just want to be a take out pizza joint, don't tell me you serve baked ziti and eggplant parm with no table service.  I will not be back.

detailedReviews.author: Pamela H Michos
detailedReviews.text:
Used to be my favorite spot- my son would eat here a few times per week as well as order pies to go. Not sure what happened but the quality of the pizza went downhill. It‚Äôs now literally paper thin to the point the structure of the pizza falls apart. Then the cheese gets burnt because there‚Äôs no pizza dough its like a paper thin slice of dough with burnt cheese. Going there in person you still may be able to get a decent slice but I stopped ordering home completely because the slices are half the size as the ones in store and the pizza either comes burnt or undercooked.
Still- they have the best eggplant slice in the area. Pretty good grandma but the regular slice and white slice have turned into a piece of paper with cheese. Understand food cost went up but they charge more than any other pizzerias in the area. Increased prices but declined quality. Also depending on who makes the pies it‚Äôs always different unfortunately. Hope they fix the pizza and go back to the old recipe
